HEADWORD: telekinesis
<hw>tel`e*ki*ne"sis</hw>
<pr>(t⟦ecr⟧l`⟦ucr⟧*k⟦icr⟧*n⟦emac⟧"s⟦icr⟧s)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>the
ability to move objects by means of thought alone, without physical
means; -- an ability claimed by certain persons, such as mediums.</def>
<note>the existence of this ability is disbelieved by most
scientists.</note>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> psychokinesis</syn>⟦br⟧
